The Dunkin' that moves slower than a snail's pace in New York City is this one! I couldn't believe it when I saw a single employee taking care of one order. Worse, it took this person fifteen minutes to take care of four sandwiches. There was absolutely no sense of multi-tasking, no sense of urgency and it was simply the ultimate test of patience as other patrons behind me left the location.  Myself -- I was only there for two large, cold bottles of water and using the washroom. The entire visit took twenty minutes and I do regret going for it, but the need to use the washroom was the biggest factor.  There wasn't any negative attitude anywhere when there was any to be shown, but it was just very... painfully slow.  It didn't help that the air conditioning/HVAC system, if they had one, was not functioning at the time anywhere outside of the washroom.
